###How to create a backend
```
1: create a folder named backend
2:cd into backend folder
3: Write the command npm init
4: access package.json in backend and delete the "test" code line and replace it with "start": "nodemon index.js"
5: Then under the "main" code line add  "type": "module",
6; in the terminal run npm install nodemon
                       npm install body-parser
                       npm install express 
6: Create index.js file
7: then write the following code in the index file
import  express  from 'express';
import bodyParser from "body-parser";

const app= express();
const PORT= 5000;
app.use(bodyParser.json());

app.listen(PORT,()=>{
    console.log("server listening on PORT: "+PORT)
});


import cors from 'cors';
 it enables communication btwn backend and frontend.
```